Patient: How much water should I drink every day for my heart condition?
Healthcare Educator: Try to limit your fluid intake to 6-8 cups a day, including all drinks and soups.

Patient: What happens if I drink more than the recommended amount?
Healthcare Educator: Too much fluid can make your heart work harder. It might worsen your heart failure symptoms.

Patient: Are there any signs to tell if I'm drinking too much?
Healthcare Educator: Yes, watch out for weight gain, swollen ankles, or feeling breathless. These signs might mean you're overdoing it.

Patient: Does it matter what kind of fluid I drink?
Healthcare Educator: Yes, avoid alcohol and keep caffeine to a minimum. Water, herbal tea or diluted juice are better.

Patient: How can I keep track of my fluid intake?
Healthcare Educator: You can use a water bottle with measurements or download an app to help keep track.